To shutdown server (otherwise threads persist):
    curl -d '{}' -H "Content-Type: application/json" -X POST http://localhost:5060/shutdown

More responsive volume control in Python
    separate receiver control thread
    HTTP inserts commands into queue
    control thread drains command queue every 100msec
        collapsing command types: volume, mode, on/off, mute, chromecast audio
        all volume requests to 1 request
	immediately update receiver status after queue drain
	otherwise updates queue every 2 seconds
Handle connection dropped
More responsive volume control in Javascript
    100msec updates while dragging, send most recent
    if(get_updates) { update status every 2 seconds }
    set interval timer on click
        dragging_volume = true
	get_updates = false
    in interval timer:
	send current volume
	set interval timer
    on release
	delete interval timer
	send current volume
	dragging_volume = false
	get_updates = true
